description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Long Term Placement Opportunity Available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nurse Team Manager – Infection Prevention Control&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse Team Manager seeking flexibility in your work pattern? Do you want to make a difference to patients quality of life?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a unique and exciting opportunity within &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; which will allow the successful candidate to gain &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;regular shifts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and valuable &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; within a unique infection prevention control environment. We have a &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Long Term Placement opportunity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; available, providing you with the chance to work &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;regular shifts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; for a &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;guaranteed period of 3 months with a possible extension for a further 6 months&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - Tatchbury Mount, Calmore&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day Rate - £20.91 per hour &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Night/Sat Rate - £27.19 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sun/Bank Holiday Rate - £33.46 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals is working in conjunction with Southern Health NHS Foundation trust who are seeking a qualified Nurses Team Manager to join the bank. NHS Professionals works in partnership with Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust to provide their temporary staffing requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Nurses Team Manager to work at Tatchbury Mount. To work with the Infection prevention control team, you will be required to make site visits across Hampshire during office hours, you must feel confident using Microsoft Office and Outlook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key parts of the role are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide IPC advice to returning services and help them interpret local and national guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Policy writing and review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Site visits to check precautions are in place and audit practice/environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) Buddy training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check Comms and guidance documents relating to COVID19&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend (still virtual at the moment) Trust meetings where IPC input is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide staff with advice on how to interpret results and care for patients with infections safely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage small IPC projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be offered a full induction, training and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to apply for this post you &lt;strong&gt;must&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Hold an IPC Qualification&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Have a minimum of 6 months experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; in a similar role held within the last 2 years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have good communication skills and demonstrate evidence of team working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to take direction and instruction and be honest and trustworthy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to work Independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive, weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHSP Stakeholder Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid annual leave and statutory maternity pay (subject to qualifying criteria)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First refusal on available shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information or an informal discussion, please contact The Southern Health Bank Team on : SHFTRecruitment@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that you will be contacted via email throughout the recruitment process, so we urge you to ensure your email address submitted is accurate and checked regularly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registration with NHS Professionals is subject to employment history and reference checking and offers of registration are therefore conditional upon the receipt of satisfactory references&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
